WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.320
Iris Press Publishers, The Adventures of Six Friends by Yulia Puchkova

00:15.320 --> 00:28.400
Chapter 1. Six Friends. There lived six little children, clever, fat, noisy, naughty, slow,

00:28.400 --> 00:37.760
and funny. They were all eight years old. Clever was a nice little girl. She was short

00:37.760 --> 00:46.640
and thin. She had long dark hair and big, brown eyes. She liked reading, and she was

00:46.640 --> 00:57.860
very clever. Fat was a nice little boy. He was short and fat. He had short fair hair

00:57.860 --> 01:09.000
and gray eyes. He liked eating very much. Noisy was a nice little girl. She was tall

01:09.000 --> 01:20.640
and slim. She had long fair hair and big, blue eyes. She liked talking, and she was very

01:20.640 --> 01:32.940
noisy. Naughty was a nice little boy. He was tall and thin. He had short curly, brown hair

01:32.940 --> 01:44.260
and big, blue eyes. He liked riding a bike, and he was very naughty. Slow was a nice little

01:44.260 --> 01:54.460
girl. She was short and plump. She had long, curly, dark hair and brown eyes. She liked

01:54.460 --> 02:06.620
wearing beautiful clothes, but she was very slow. Funny was a nice little boy. He was tall

02:06.620 --> 02:17.940
and thin. He had short fair hair and dark eyes. He liked walking, and he was very funny. They were

02:17.940 --> 02:44.180
in the same form, and they were friends. Chapter 2 Birthday Present

02:44.180 --> 02:54.500
It was Sunday, and it was Fat's birthday. In the morning, his mum and dad came into his room.

02:54.500 --> 03:06.460
Wake up, dear. Happy birthday to you, they said. Here is your present. Fat opened his eyes and saw

03:06.460 --> 03:17.580
a bike. It was very beautiful. It was red and blue, and had very big wheels. Oh, thank you very

03:17.580 --> 03:28.380
much, cried Fat. Can I go to the yard and cycle? Yes, you can, his parents said. But come home at

03:28.380 --> 03:36.300
noon. Your friends are coming at three o'clock. You must tidy your room, lay the table, and cook

03:36.300 --> 03:47.980
pizza. Okay, mummy, said Fat. Don't worry, I know I must do it. Fat's mum looked at him and said,

03:47.980 --> 03:56.940
Oh dear, look out of the window. It's sunny and warm. Take off your trousers, jumper, and trainers.

03:57.740 --> 04:07.580
Put on some shorts, a t-shirt, and sandals. Fat took off the warm clothes, and put on his yellow

04:07.580 --> 04:16.940
shorts, a red t-shirt, and green sandals. Oh, I look cute, he said, when he looked in the mirror,

04:17.740 --> 04:31.900
and he went downstairs with his bike.

04:31.900 --> 04:52.700
Chapter three. In the yard. In the yard, he saw his friends, funny and naughty. They were on the

04:52.700 --> 05:03.100
playground. Hi, cried Fat. Oh, Fat, we're glad to see you. Happy birthday.

05:04.620 --> 05:13.420
Why do you look like traffic lights? Left naughty. I don't. I look cute, said Fat.

05:14.380 --> 05:26.300
What have you got? Asked naughty. I've got a bike. It's my birthday present. Oh, great. Can I ride it?

05:26.300 --> 05:34.620
Asked naughty. Oh, naughty. But I want to ride it myself, said Fat.

05:35.420 --> 05:46.620
Okay, said naughty. So Fat climbed upon his bike, and started cycling. 

05:46.720 --> 05:51.120
There was a small gate in the fence of the yard. 

05:51.220 --> 05:54.620
Fat wanted to ride through the gate. 

05:54.720 --> 05:58.220
But the gate was too small for him. 

05:58.320 --> 06:03.520
So his bike went through, and Fat got stuck in the gate.

06:03.180 --> 06:09.660
Help me. Help me. Cried Fat. Catch my bike.

06:10.940 --> 06:24.380
Funny and naughty, ran to catch the bike. It wasn't easy, but at last they did it. They climbed upon the bike, and came back to Fat.

06:25.180 --> 06:34.380
Oh, now help me, please. I can't hang here like this. I must be at home at noon, cried Fat.

06:35.580 --> 06:48.180
Funny and naughty, ran up to him. Oh, you look so funny. Laughs funny. Don't laugh. Please get me down, cried Fat.

06:49.180 --> 06:56.180
Funny and naughty first pulled him, then pushed him, but nothing helped.

06:57.180 --> 07:06.180
Run to my mum, cried Fat. So funny and naughty, ran to Fat's mum very fast.

07:07.180 --> 07:15.180
They told her all the story. She took a bottle of olive oil and ran to her poor son.

07:16.180 --> 07:22.180
When she came up to him, she opened the bottle and poured the oil down on Fat.

07:23.180 --> 07:26.180
What are you doing? shouted Fat.

07:27.180 --> 07:33.180
I'm helping you, dear, answered his mum. Oh, I'm falling.

07:34.180 --> 07:38.180
Cried Fat and fell down on the grass.

07:45.180 --> 07:49.180
Fats birthday party.

07:50.180 --> 08:14.180
So Fat went home with his mum and his bike. Mum put him into the bathtub and washed him with a lot of soap.

08:16.180 --> 08:20.180
When he was clean, it was half past two.

08:21.180 --> 08:29.180
Oh, dear, cried Fat's mum. Your friends are coming soon and we are not ready.

08:31.180 --> 08:38.180
So Fat went to tidy his room and his mum went to cook pizza and lay the table.

08:39.180 --> 08:47.180
At ten past three, two of Fat's friends came. They were funny and naughty.

08:48.180 --> 08:56.180
Happy birthday to you, said naughty and gave Fat a big bottle of olive oil.

08:57.180 --> 09:06.180
The boys laughed, but Fat was angry. He wanted to cry, but his friend said,

09:07.180 --> 09:15.180
Don't be angry. It's a joke. Best wishes on your ninth birthday.

09:16.180 --> 09:31.180
And they gave Fat a big box. When Fat opened it, saw CD, a book about animals and a big jar of jam.

09:32.180 --> 09:42.180
Thank you, friends, said Fat and smiled. They sat down to watch a cartoon. Soon came noisy and clever.

09:43.180 --> 09:52.180
They gave Fat a big cake, an apple pie and a box of chocolate. Fat was happy.

09:53.180 --> 09:58.180
It was half past four, but slow wasn't there.

09:59.180 --> 10:02.180
Where is slow, asked Fat?

10:03.180 --> 10:13.180
We don't know, answered the children. Let's phone her. And they phoned slow. But she wasn't at home.

10:14.180 --> 10:22.180
So the children sat down at the table. They ate and drank, talked and watched films and cartoons.

10:23.180 --> 10:32.180
Then they danced and sang and clever played the piano. After that, they listened to new CDs.

10:33.180 --> 10:37.180
It was a very merry birthday party.

10:53.180 --> 11:00.180
Chapter 5 – Slow is Coming

11:01.180 --> 11:10.180
Hey, so at four o'clock I started putting on this fifth dress and I was ready at half past four.

11:11.180 --> 11:20.180
I took my present for you and went downstairs. At quarter to five, I was in the yard.

11:21.180 --> 11:32.180
It was raining and I walked very slowly. I didn't want to make my beautiful shoes, socks and dress dirty.

11:33.180 --> 11:35.180
And here I am.

11:37.180 --> 11:38.180
Be.

11:40.180 --> 11:48.180
It was quarter to seven when slow came in. You are late, said Fat.

11:49.180 --> 11:54.180
Yes, I'm terribly sorry, said Slow.

11:55.180 --> 11:58.180
But you look beautiful, said Fat.

11:59.180 --> 12:04.180
Thank you, said Slow. It is the fifth dress.

12:06.180 --> 12:07.180
See.

12:08.180 --> 12:17.180
Slow gave Fat her present. It was a jar of honey, a kilo of strawberries and an interesting book with a lopper.

12:18.180 --> 12:25.180
Fat of pictures. Fat thanked her and they went into the room.

12:26.180 --> 12:27.180
D.

12:29.180 --> 12:35.180
I put on the first dress from twelve till half past twelve.

12:36.180 --> 12:44.180
But I looked fat in it. I took it off from half past twelve till one o'clock.

12:44.180 --> 12:53.180
Then I tried a second dress. But it was too long and covered my beautiful shoes.

12:54.180 --> 12:59.180
The third was red and I haven't got red shoes.

13:00.180 --> 13:05.180
The fourth was old and too short.

13:14.180 --> 13:16.180
D.

13:24.180 --> 13:28.180
Chapter six. Good friend.

13:29.180 --> 13:37.180
It was Monday morning. Fat was in bed. His mum came to wake him up.

13:38.180 --> 13:43.180
Fat could hear her, but he couldn't get up.

13:44.180 --> 13:47.180
He had a terrible stomachache.

13:48.180 --> 13:57.180
Oh no! It is your birthday party. You ate too many sweets yesterday, cried his mother.

13:58.180 --> 14:01.180
She phoned Fat's teacher.

14:02.180 --> 14:12.180
Mrs. Smart, my son is ill. He can't go to school. He has got a terrible stomachache.

14:12.180 --> 14:22.180
I see, said Mrs. Smart. I hope he feels better soon. I think it's his birthday party.

14:23.180 --> 14:34.180
So Fat didn't go to school. He stayed in bed. In the afternoon, his friend Naughty visited him.

14:35.180 --> 14:41.180
How are you, Fat? asked Naughty. You look awful.

14:42.180 --> 14:47.180
I'm not well. My stomach hurt.

14:48.180 --> 14:57.180
And said Fat. I see, said Naughty. So you mustn't eat your jam, honey, and sweets?

14:58.180 --> 15:02.180
No. I mustn't. And said Fat.

15:02.180 --> 15:10.180
And it's awful. I like sweets, cakes, pies, and chocolate so much.

15:11.180 --> 15:22.180
I can help you, said Naughty. I can eat them up. But Fat started, but stopped.

15:23.180 --> 15:32.180
Okay. Eat them up. I am too fat. And I have got a stomachache.

15:33.180 --> 15:44.180
So Naughty sat down at the table and started eating. Fat closed his eyes. He didn't want to see that.

15:45.180 --> 15:54.180
First, Naughty ate all the cakes and slices of the pie. Then all the sweets and chocolate.

15:55.180 --> 15:58.180
Fat opened his eyes.

15:59.180 --> 16:07.180
Thank you, he said. You are a very good friend. I hope your stomach is stronger than mine.

16:08.180 --> 16:20.180
On Tuesday, Fat went to school. But Naughty wasn't there. After school, Fat visited his friend.

16:21.180 --> 16:28.180
Naughty was in bed. He had a terrible toothache.

16:37.180 --> 16:42.180
After school, Naughty was in bed.

16:49.180 --> 16:55.180
Chapter 7. Catching Butterflies

16:56.180 --> 17:04.180
It was summer. The children were happy. There was a big field near their town.

17:04.180 --> 17:08.180
They went to the field to catch butterflies.

17:09.180 --> 17:16.180
Wow. Look. What a beautiful butterfly. Cried noisy.

17:17.180 --> 17:26.180
I think I can catch it. Naughty ran after the butterfly. She ran and shouted.

17:26.180 --> 17:32.180
Oh, how fast it is flying. What beautiful spots it has got.

17:33.180 --> 17:42.180
Noisy, be quiet, said clever. Don't shout all the time. The butterfly can hear you.

17:43.180 --> 17:50.180
Nonsense, said noisy. First, I can't be quiet because I'm noisy.

17:51.180 --> 17:59.180
Second, the butterfly can hear me, but it can't understand that I want to catch it.

18:00.180 --> 18:06.180
Why, asked the children. Because it doesn't speak English.

18:08.180 --> 18:16.180
No, it doesn't speak English, but it can understand English, said clever.

18:17.180 --> 18:25.180
It is an English butterfly. My dog is English, too. She doesn't speak English.

18:25.180 --> 18:33.180
But she understands it very well. Oh, really, asked noisy.

18:34.180 --> 18:42.180
Then I must learn French or Spanish. I hope our butterflies can't understand these languages.

18:55.180 --> 19:16.180
Chapter 8. Dogs and Cats. Fat had a cat. His name was Fluffy.

19:17.180 --> 19:21.180
Fat loved him very much.

19:22.180 --> 19:32.180
He went with Fluffy to the park every day. They usually walked in the park in the afternoon.

19:33.180 --> 19:42.180
It was Thursday. It was time to go to the park. But fat didn't go.

19:43.180 --> 19:50.180
Fat? It's time to go for a walk with Fluffy, his mother said.

19:51.180 --> 19:59.180
I can't, mum. I'm still doing my homework. I've got a lot of homework today, said fat.

20:00.180 --> 20:04.180
Okay, go later, said his mum.

20:05.180 --> 20:11.180
It was seven o'clock in the evening when fat's homework was ready.

20:12.180 --> 20:16.180
He took Fluffy in his arms and off they went.

20:17.180 --> 20:25.180
They came to the park and sat down on the grass. Suddenly, fat saw clever.

20:26.180 --> 20:29.180
She was with her dog, Dolly.

20:30.180 --> 20:37.180
Hey, clever. Shouted fat. Come here. Let's play together.

20:38.180 --> 20:47.180
Now clever saw fat. But at the same time, clever's dog saw fat's cat.

20:48.180 --> 20:58.180
Dolly was very angry. She didn't like cats. In fact, she hated cats.

21:00.180 --> 21:11.180
So she barked and ran to Fluffy. Fluffy wasn't silly. In fact, he was a very clever cat.

21:12.180 --> 21:16.180
He ran fast to the nearest tree and climbed it up.

21:17.180 --> 21:23.180
Now Fluffy sat in the tree and Dolly jumped and barked under the tree.

21:24.180 --> 21:32.180
Clever and fat were under the tree too. They didn't know what to do.

21:33.180 --> 21:41.180
Take away your dog, cried fat. I can't, cried clever. She's stronger than me.

21:42.180 --> 21:49.180
Do it yourself, please. Or climb up the tree and take your cat down.

21:50.180 --> 21:58.180
I can't, said fat. Your dog is very angry and she is barking.

21:59.180 --> 22:02.180
She can bite me. I'm afraid.

22:20.180 --> 22:25.180
Chapter 9. Great idea.

22:27.180 --> 22:30.180
At that moment, they saw funny.

22:32.180 --> 22:38.180
Hey, funny. Help us. Clever and fat, shouted.

22:39.180 --> 22:42.180
Funny saw Dolly and Fluffy.

22:43.180 --> 22:54.180
Oh, I see, he said. Your pets are not good friends. But what can I do?

22:55.180 --> 23:04.180
Get another cat, said clever. Okay, said funny and ran away.

23:05.180 --> 23:12.180
Soon, he came back. He had a cat in his arms.

23:13.180 --> 23:21.180
Show the cat to Dolly, commanded clever, and put it on the grass next to her.

23:22.180 --> 23:27.180
Funny, showed the cat to Dolly and put it on the grass.

23:28.180 --> 23:32.180
Dolly looked at the cat for a moment and ran after it.

23:33.180 --> 23:36.180
And clever ran after Dolly.

23:37.180 --> 23:45.180
But the cat wasn't sillier than Fluffy. It ran up to a tree and climbed it up very fast.

23:47.180 --> 23:52.180
Thank you, funny, said fat. Now he wasn't afraid.

23:53.180 --> 24:01.180
He climbed up the tree and took Fluffy down. But poor clever was under another tree now.

24:03.180 --> 24:07.180
Oh, no, she said. That doesn't help.

24:09.180 --> 24:16.180
I can run to your parents, said funny. But they're at work now, said clever.

24:17.180 --> 24:25.180
I know what to do, said funny. Clever. Your house is near the park on the left.

24:26.180 --> 24:34.180
I can catch another cat, show it to Dolly, and put it on the grass on the left of this tree.

24:35.180 --> 24:41.180
I can do it again and again, and we can get to your house soon.

24:42.180 --> 24:50.180
That's a great idea, smiled fat. I'm sorry, friends, but I must go.

24:51.180 --> 24:54.180
And he went away, very fast.

24:56.180 --> 25:05.180
When the twelfth cat was in a twelfth tree, clever and funny were opposite Clever's house.

25:06.180 --> 25:10.180
Clever saw her mum through an open window.

25:11.180 --> 25:17.180
Oh, mummy, you're back. Come here, shouted Clever.

25:18.180 --> 25:21.180
Clever's mother ran out and took Dolly away.

25:23.180 --> 25:26.180
Clever told her all the story.

25:28.180 --> 25:31.180
Poor children laughed Clever's mother.

25:32.180 --> 25:36.180
Now let's have tea with sweets and forget cats.

25:47.180 --> 26:01.180
Chapped to ten noisy neighbours.

26:03.180 --> 26:08.180
On Friday, Clever and Slow went to noisy.

26:09.180 --> 26:16.180
When they came in, they could hear a terrible noise in one of the rooms upstairs.

26:17.180 --> 26:20.180
They went there and saw noisy.

26:22.180 --> 26:26.180
What are you doing? Asked the girls.

26:27.180 --> 26:33.180
I'm asking my neighbours to be quiet, answered noisy.

26:34.180 --> 26:39.180
Why must they be quiet? Asked the girls.

26:40.180 --> 26:46.180
Because my little brother is sleeping, answered noisy.

26:48.180 --> 26:52.180
Are your neighbours making a noise? Asked Clever?

26:54.180 --> 27:03.180
No, they aren't yet, but I'm telling them that my brother is sleeping and that they mustn't make a noise.

27:04.180 --> 27:09.180
With these words, noisy shouted out of the window.

27:10.180 --> 27:21.180
Mrs. Stout, can you hear me? My little brother is sleeping. Please don't make a noise till three o'clock.

27:22.180 --> 27:31.180
And then, Mr. Dixon, can you hear me? My little brother is sleeping.

27:32.180 --> 27:37.180
Please be quiet till three o'clock.

27:38.180 --> 27:44.180
How many neighbours have you got? Asked Slow.

27:45.180 --> 27:52.180
A lot. And they don't always hear me from the first time, answered noisy.

27:53.180 --> 28:01.180
I see, said Clever. Don't you see noisy, that it's you who is making the noise?

28:02.180 --> 28:10.180
I think you should walk to your neighbours. You shouldn't shout to them when your brother is sleeping.

28:12.180 --> 28:16.180
And I don't think he is, said Slow.

28:23.180 --> 28:40.180
Chapter 11. In the Country.

28:42.180 --> 28:49.180
On Saturday, all the children went to the country together with their parents.

28:50.180 --> 28:53.180
The weather was sunny and hot.

28:59.180 --> 29:04.180
When they came to the place, the children went to the field to play.

29:05.180 --> 29:09.180
And their parents started working in the garden.

29:12.180 --> 29:16.180
When the children came up to the field, funny cried.

29:17.180 --> 29:22.180
Oh! Look at those big white dogs in the field.

29:23.180 --> 29:25.180
And they're eating grass.

29:27.180 --> 29:31.180
How funny! Clever looked at him and smiled.

29:33.180 --> 29:38.180
Is it the first time you are in the country? She asked.

29:39.180 --> 29:48.180
They are not dogs. Those animals are goats, said Clever.

29:49.180 --> 29:59.180
Oh! Goats! Now I know what they are like. I can make a poem about them. Listen.

30:00.180 --> 30:07.180
Those big goats have got white goats. They're eating the grass.

30:09.180 --> 30:11.180
And looking at us.

30:13.180 --> 30:19.180
Well done, said Clever. But I think they aren't looking at us.

30:24.180 --> 30:28.180
And Naughty is looking at you, said Slow.

30:30.180 --> 30:32.180
Naughty was red.

30:33.180 --> 30:38.180
I'm not looking at her. I'm listening to her, he said.

30:40.180 --> 30:42.180
Let's go to the river, said Clever.

30:44.180 --> 30:47.180
But I haven't got my swimsuit on, said noisy.

30:48.180 --> 30:51.180
And I haven't got my swimming trunks, said Funny.

30:57.180 --> 30:59.180
The water in the river is too cold.

31:00.180 --> 31:07.180
But we can see horses and cows there. They usually go there to drink water.

31:09.180 --> 31:13.180
When the children came to the river, Clever said sadly.

31:14.180 --> 31:21.180
Oh! I can't see any cows or horses. I only can see a sheep.

31:22.180 --> 31:30.180
Oh! A ship? Cried Funny. We can sail on it. It's better than cows and horses.

31:35.180 --> 31:39.180
Funny. Look. It's not a ship. It's a sheep.

31:51.180 --> 31:53.180
Oh! A ship.

32:00.180 --> 32:02.180
Chapter 12

32:03.180 --> 32:04.180
At the zoo.

32:07.180 --> 32:13.180
In August, the children and their parents came back to town.

32:14.180 --> 32:20.180
It was very boring in town after the merry summer in the countryside.

32:21.180 --> 32:26.180
So on Sunday, the children went to the zoo.

32:27.180 --> 32:28.180
Oh, look.

32:29.180 --> 32:33.180
There is a cheetah in the cage over there, Cried Funny.

32:34.180 --> 32:36.180
Yes, I can see it.

32:37.180 --> 32:41.180
It's the fastest animal on the land, said Clever.

32:42.180 --> 32:48.180
But it's not the strongest. I think lion is stronger, said noisy.

32:49.180 --> 32:52.180
But it's slower, said slow.

32:53.180 --> 32:57.180
But it's not the slowest animal, smiled fat.

32:59.180 --> 33:03.180
Who is the slowest? asked noisy.

33:04.180 --> 33:09.180
Slow is the slowest, laughed naughty and looked at slow.

33:10.180 --> 33:17.180
I'm not the slowest. The snail is slower than me, said slow.

33:18.180 --> 33:26.180
Yes, but it has got only one leg, and you have got two, said naughty.

33:27.180 --> 33:33.180
Yes, but it's better to have one leg than it's not right or left.

33:35.180 --> 33:40.180
And I always mix them up when I put on my shoes, so it's easier for the snail.

33:41.180 --> 33:44.180
It can't mix up its legs, said slow.

33:45.180 --> 33:52.180
Naughty, smiled at slow. That's a pity the snail hasn't got any shoes, he laughed.

33:54.180 --> 33:59.180
Oh, I can see a panda over there, Cried Funny.

34:00.180 --> 34:02.180
What is it eating?

34:03.180 --> 34:07.180
It's eating bamboo leaves, said Clever.

34:08.180 --> 34:10.180
Are they sweet, asked fat?

34:11.180 --> 34:14.180
Do you want to try them, asked naughty?

34:15.180 --> 34:16.180
Yes, I do.

34:17.180 --> 34:22.180
Please ask the panda for a leaf or two for me, said fat and smiled.

34:23.180 --> 34:25.180
Don't be greedy.

34:26.180 --> 34:30.180
You are much fatter than this poor panda, answered naughty.

34:40.180 --> 34:42.180
What is it eating?

34:50.180 --> 34:53.180
Chapter 13, Python.

34:55.180 --> 34:59.180
Suddenly, slow screamed.

35:00.180 --> 35:03.180
What's the matter, asked Clever?

35:04.180 --> 35:07.180
Look, there's a long snake in a tree.

35:07.180 --> 35:09.180
Slow looked afraid.

35:10.180 --> 35:13.180
All the children looked at the tree.

35:14.180 --> 35:18.180
Don't worry, it's a Python, it's sleeping.

35:19.180 --> 35:22.180
It is beautiful, said Clever.

35:23.180 --> 35:28.180
Or handsome, if it is he, said naughty.

35:29.180 --> 35:34.180
Noisy looked at them and said, why is it here?

35:35.180 --> 35:38.180
What is it doing here in the tree?

35:39.180 --> 35:42.180
Who is it? Where is it from?

35:44.180 --> 35:47.180
I think it lives here in the zoo, said Clever.

35:48.180 --> 35:51.180
I hope somebody is taking him for a walk.

35:53.180 --> 35:57.180
The children looked around and saw two women.

35:58.180 --> 36:02.180
The Python is theirs, shouted fat.

36:03.180 --> 36:09.180
Clever came up to the women, pointed to the Python and asked, is it yours?

36:10.180 --> 36:16.180
The women looked up, screamed and ran away, very fast.

36:17.180 --> 36:22.180
Oops, it's not theirs, but why did they run away?

36:23.180 --> 36:24.180
Asked funny.

36:25.180 --> 36:29.180
I think they ran to find the zookeeper, answered slow.

36:30.180 --> 36:34.180
So we must guard the Python till the zookeeper comes.

36:35.180 --> 36:43.180
So the children sat down on the grass, took out their sandwiches and started their lunch.

36:59.180 --> 37:06.180
Chapter 14

37:07.180 --> 37:10.180
Lunch for Python

37:12.180 --> 37:19.180
So, looked at the Python and said, I think the poor Python is very hungry.

37:21.180 --> 37:23.180
Let's give it a piece of ham.

37:24.180 --> 37:28.180
Oh yes, a great idea, cried the children.

37:29.180 --> 37:33.180
But how can we do that? It's very high in the tree.

37:35.180 --> 37:39.180
I can climb up the tree and give it the food, said fat.

37:40.180 --> 37:45.180
Can you? As the children, you're very brave.

37:45.180 --> 37:50.180
Fat was very proud.

37:51.180 --> 38:00.180
He put his food on the grass, took a big piece of ham out of his sandwich and started climbing up the tree.

38:01.180 --> 38:06.180
But it was difficult to do it with the piece of ham in his hand.

38:07.180 --> 38:14.180
So fat said, take the ham and throw it back to me when I'm up.

38:15.180 --> 38:20.180
He climbed and climbed and climbed.

38:21.180 --> 38:24.180
Now he was high in the tree.

38:25.180 --> 38:31.180
But the Python was on a thin branch, at the very end of it.

38:32.180 --> 38:37.180
So fat started climbing up that branch.

38:37.180 --> 38:45.180
Suddenly, there was an awful noise, and all the three of them fell down on the grass.

38:46.180 --> 38:52.180
The Python, the branch, and fat.

38:53.180 --> 38:56.180
Are you okay? Asked funny.

38:57.180 --> 39:00.180
Yes, said fat. I only hit my leg.

39:00.180 --> 39:03.180
All is well that ends well, said clever.

39:04.180 --> 39:09.180
The Python is here, and the ham is here. Now we can feed it easily.

39:11.180 --> 39:20.180
The Python opened its eyes, smelled the ham, ate it up, and closed its eyes again.

39:21.180 --> 39:24.180
What a nice Python, said slow.

39:25.180 --> 39:27.180
It's so cute and quiet.

39:28.180 --> 39:31.180
I think we should give it some water to drink.

39:51.180 --> 39:53.180
Chapter 15.

39:54.180 --> 39:56.180
Zookeeper comes.

39:58.180 --> 40:04.180
At that moment, they saw tall man. He looked very angry.

40:05.180 --> 40:10.180
He ran up to them and shouted, what are you doing here?

40:11.180 --> 40:14.180
You mustn't climb trees in the zoo.

40:15.180 --> 40:21.180
But we're not climbing trees. We're guarding your Python, said the children.

40:22.180 --> 40:27.180
The zookeeper looked down on the grass and saw the Python.

40:28.180 --> 40:34.180
Now everyone saw that it was a very long and thick Python.

40:36.180 --> 40:41.180
Oh, good children. I'm sorry. Thank you very much.

40:42.180 --> 40:49.180
Can you help me to carry the Python back to its cage? Asked the zookeeper.

40:50.180 --> 40:54.180
Yes, we can, cried the children.

40:55.180 --> 41:00.180
And everyone who was at the zoo that day could see a funny line of people.

41:01.180 --> 41:05.180
The first was the zookeeper. The second was fat.

41:06.180 --> 41:09.180
The third and the fourth were slow and noisy.

41:10.180 --> 41:13.180
The fifth and the sixth were funny and clever.

41:14.180 --> 41:16.180
And the seventh was naughty.

41:17.180 --> 41:19.180
They went one after another.

41:20.180 --> 41:24.180
And each of them held a piece of the long Python in their hands.

41:24.180 --> 41:25.180
In their hands.

41:45.180 --> 41:48.180
Chapter 16. Back to school.

41:49.180 --> 41:55.180
It was autumn again. It was time to go to school.

41:56.180 --> 42:02.180
The children came to school on Monday. They had five lessons.

42:03.180 --> 42:09.180
History, science, art, English, and PE.

42:10.180 --> 42:17.180
What is your favorite subject funny? Asked naughty.

42:18.180 --> 42:23.180
I like PE answered funny. Do you?

42:24.180 --> 42:27.180
Yes, I like PE too.

42:28.180 --> 42:31.180
But my favorite subject is art.

42:32.180 --> 42:35.180
I like drawing and painting very much.

42:35.180 --> 42:38.180
And you fat and clever?

42:39.180 --> 42:44.180
I like science because I like animals, said fat.

42:46.180 --> 42:52.180
I like all the subjects, but my favorite is history, said clever.

42:53.180 --> 42:57.180
I don't like history. It's boring, said noisy.

42:59.180 --> 43:02.180
How do you know? You never listen to the teacher.

43:03.180 --> 43:05.180
You always talk, said slow.

43:07.180 --> 43:15.180
Yes, I always do when I sit with Mary. But at history lessons, I sit with quiet.

43:16.180 --> 43:19.180
And she is very boring, said noisy.

43:22.180 --> 43:26.180
After science, the children had art.

43:27.180 --> 43:33.180
The teacher of art, Mr. Pencil, was a very kind and funny man.

43:34.180 --> 43:40.180
He asked the children to sit down and said, I'm glad to see you again.

43:41.180 --> 43:45.180
Today, we are going to draw or paint animals.

43:47.180 --> 43:51.180
I hope you all have got a favorite animal.

43:52.180 --> 43:58.180
Maybe it's your pet or a farm animal. Maybe you saw it at the zoo.

43:59.180 --> 44:01.180
Now start.

44:03.180 --> 44:07.180
All the children started drawing or painting.

44:08.180 --> 44:14.180
Mr. Pencil walked around the classroom and looked at the children's pictures.

44:15.180 --> 44:21.180
What are you drawing slow? He asked when he came up to slow.

44:22.180 --> 44:27.180
I'm drawing a panda. I saw it at the zoo, said slow.

44:28.180 --> 44:32.180
And what are you drawing? Funny, asked Mr. Pencil.

44:33.180 --> 44:38.180
I'm drawing a goat. I saw it in the country, said funny.

44:39.180 --> 44:42.180
Clever painted her dog, Dolly.

44:43.180 --> 44:49.180
Noisy drew the python from the zoo. Fat drew his cat, fluffy.

44:50.180 --> 44:56.180
Then Mr. Pencil came up to naughty. He saw a picture of a man.

44:58.180 --> 45:06.180
Why are you painting a man? I asked you to paint your favorite animal, said Mr. Pencil.

45:06.180 --> 45:07.180
Angrily.

45:09.180 --> 45:18.180
Yes, I know, answered naughty. But our science teacher said at the lesson that people are animals too.

45:19.180 --> 45:25.180
And you are my favorite teacher. I'm painting you, Mr. Pencil.

45:26.180 --> 45:27.180
Smiled naughty.

45:36.180 --> 45:54.180
Chapter 17. Those rolls and buns.

45:57.180 --> 46:03.180
It was Tuesday afternoon. Fat walked along the street.

46:04.180 --> 46:07.180
Suddenly, he saw funny.

46:09.180 --> 46:13.180
Hey, funny. Hello, fat.

46:14.180 --> 46:17.180
Where are you going, asked funny?

46:18.180 --> 46:22.180
First, I'm going to the bakers to buy some rolls and buns.

46:23.180 --> 46:31.180
And then, I'm going to the grocers. I must buy some flour and some sugar for mum.

46:32.180 --> 46:36.180
Come with me, answered fat and smiled.

46:37.180 --> 46:41.180
Oh, fat. I don't think rolls and buns are good for you.

46:42.180 --> 46:45.180
You mustn't eat them every day, said funny.

46:47.180 --> 46:54.180
Why? I'm already fat. They are so tasty.

46:55.180 --> 46:59.180
And fat smiled again.

47:00.180 --> 47:05.180
So, you want to be fatter, I see, said funny.

47:06.180 --> 47:11.180
No, I don't. I can't run well, because I'm too fat.

47:12.180 --> 47:16.180
But I can't live without rolls and buns, cried fat.

47:17.180 --> 47:22.180
Listen, fat. I'm your best friend, said funny.

47:23.180 --> 47:27.180
I shouldn't go to the bakers and buy rolls and buns for you.

47:28.180 --> 47:31.180
I shouldn't do what is bad for you.

47:32.180 --> 47:36.180
Besides, I must go to the butchers to buy some meat.

47:37.180 --> 47:38.180
Buy.

47:40.180 --> 47:46.180
Buy, said fat, sadly and walked on.

47:47.180 --> 47:50.180
But funny, didn't go to the butchers.

47:51.180 --> 47:55.180
He turned left into another street and then turned right

47:55.180 --> 47:59.180
and ran to the bakers very fast.

48:01.180 --> 48:05.180
He ran into the bakers shop, closed the door and shouted.

48:06.180 --> 48:10.180
Mr. Pie, you must know my friend fat.

48:11.180 --> 48:16.180
He's going here now. He's going to buy rolls and buns.

48:17.180 --> 48:20.180
But he's already too fat.

48:21.180 --> 48:24.180
Please, don't sell them to him.

48:26.180 --> 48:28.180
But how can I do that?

48:29.180 --> 48:31.180
Asked Mr. Pie.

48:32.180 --> 48:36.180
You must take all the rolls and buns away from the counters.

48:37.180 --> 48:40.180
Please, Mr. Pie, do it for me and for him.

48:41.180 --> 48:44.180
I can help you, cried funny.

48:45.180 --> 48:52.180
Okay, said Mr. Pie, and they took away all fat's favorite foods.

48:52.180 --> 48:53.180
Mm-hmm.

49:12.180 --> 49:16.180
Chapter 18, Helpful Woman.

49:17.180 --> 49:22.180
When fat came in, he didn't see any rolls and buns in the shop.

49:24.180 --> 49:27.180
Good afternoon, Mr. Pie.

49:28.180 --> 49:32.180
Can I buy some rolls and buns? Asked fat.

49:33.180 --> 49:40.180
I'm very sorry, but we haven't got any rolls and buns at the moment, said Mr. Pie.

49:41.180 --> 49:45.180
Oh no, cried fat. I need them so much.

49:47.180 --> 49:53.180
I'm terribly sorry, repeated Mr. Pie, and he was really very sorry.

49:55.180 --> 50:00.180
Fat went out of the shop. He turned left and went to the grocers.

50:01.180 --> 50:07.180
He was very sad. He wanted rolls and buns, very much.

50:08.180 --> 50:12.180
In the evening, funny phoned fat.

50:13.180 --> 50:18.180
Hello, fat. What are you doing? He asked.

50:19.180 --> 50:26.180
I'm having tea. Come to me, said fat. His voice was happy.

50:28.180 --> 50:36.180
Hooray, smiled funny. He can live without rolls and buns, and he can be happy.

50:38.180 --> 50:42.180
He ran downstairs and on to Fat's house.

50:43.180 --> 50:48.180
When fat opened the door, funny opened his mouth.

50:50.180 --> 50:55.180
What's the matter with you, funny? You don't look happy, ask fat.

50:57.180 --> 51:05.180
Where did you get that bun? Asked funny, looking at the big bun in Fat's hand.

51:05.180 --> 51:08.180
Did you buy it at the bakers?

51:10.180 --> 51:14.180
Oh no, there were no rolls and buns there.

51:15.180 --> 51:20.180
But then I went to the grocers to buy some flour and sugar for mom.

51:21.180 --> 51:27.180
There, I met a very nice woman. She likes rolls and buns too.

51:28.180 --> 51:32.180
But she doesn't usually buy them. She cooks them.

51:33.180 --> 51:40.180
She taught me how to cook tasty buns. She is here. She is helping me.

51:41.180 --> 51:46.180
I think you know her. She is Mrs. Pie.

